    <h1>UX5000 and Aspire FAQ</h1>
    <h4>Review Ring Tones</h4>
    <ol>
        <li>Press [CALL 1]</li>
        <li>Press [8] [1] [1]</li>
        <li>Press [1] to listen to intercom ring tone or [2] for outside line ring tone</li>
        <li>Press numbers 1-8 to listen to ring tones</li>
        <li>Press [SPK] to hang up</li>
    </ol>
    <h4>Change Ring Tones</h4>
    <ol>
        <li>Press [CALL 1]</li>
        <li>Press [8] [2] [0]</li>
        <li>Press [1] to set intercom ring tone or [2] for outside line ring tone.</li>
        <li>Press number 1-8 to select ring tone</li>
        <li>Press [HOLD] to save desired tone</li>
        <li>Press [SPK] to hang up</li>
    </ol>
    <h4>Name Change on Phones</h4>
    <ol>
        <li>Press [CALL 1]</li>
        <li>Enter [8] [0] [0]</li>
        <li>Enter the extension number for the name that you want to change &ndash; you will
            see the extension number and the name that is currently programmed</li>
        <li>Press [HOLD] to save this entry OR enter the new name as you would if you were doing
            it on your cell phone.<br />
            <strong>Example:</strong> <em>Service</em><br />
            S = press 7, 4 times; E = press 3, twice; R = press 7, 3 times; V = press 8, 3 times<br />
            I = press 4, 3 times; C = press 2, 3 times; E = press 3, twice</li>
    </ol>
    <p>
        <strong>Helpful Hints:</strong>
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>If you need to back up, press the CONF key.</li>
        <li>If you need a space, press the pound (#) key twice.</li>
        <li>If you have two letters of the same key in a row, press the pound (#) key once to
            save each letter.</li>
        <li>Press [HOLD] to save the new name</li>
        <li>You will hear three beeps confirming your change</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
        <strong>NOTE:</strong> This changes the programming in the phone system and on the
        display of the phones, but does not necessarily change it in the voice mail.
    </p>
    <h4>Programming One-touch Buttons "Solid Silver Buttons"</h4>
    <ol>
        <li>Press [CALL 1]</li>
        <li>Press [8] [5] [5]</li>
        <li>Press the button to be programmed</li>
        <li>Enter the telephone number OR Code to be stored<br />
            <strong>NOTE:</strong> If the number is a telephone number, enter [9] first</li>
        <li>Press [HOLD] to save</li>
        <li>Press [SPK] to hang up</li>
    </ol>
    <h4>Background Music</h4>
    <ol>
        <li>Press [CALL 1]</li>
        <li>Enter [8] [2] [5]</li>
        <li>Press [SPK]</li>
    </ol>
    <h4>Changing the Date/Time on your Phone System</h4>
    <ol>
        <li>Press [CALL 1]</li>
        <li>Dial [8] [2] [8]</li>
        <li>Enter the time in Military time (HHMM)</li>
        <li>Press [SPK] (this will save your changes)</li>
    </ol>
    <h4>Conference Calls</h4>
    <ol>
        <li>Place or answer a call</li>
        <li>Press [CONF]</li>
        <li>Dial number (either extension or "9" and outside number)</li>
        <li>Press [CONF]</li>
        <li>When all parties have been called, press [CONF] again (this connects all callers
            together)</li>
    </ol>
    <p>
        <strong>NOTE:</strong> You may dial the number and press [CONF] (steps 3 &amp; 4) as
        many times as needed. Maximum capacity is 32 callers on the line &ndash; be sure you have
        enough lines to handle the total number of callers. (i.e. if you have 6 lines and
        have 7 people (yourself and 6 others) on the call, no one else can call your business
        as all your lines will be busy. If you require more people on a call than you have
        lines, or don't want to use too many lines, call 810-743-6900 and ask your Customer
        Advocate about option for larger conference calls.
    </p>
